-- Spain’s Soria Has No Plan to Raise Power Prices Now, ABC Says
-- B y   A n g e l i n e   B e n o i t
-- 2011-12-25T12:29:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-25/spain-s-soria-has-no-plan-to-raise-power-prices-now-abc-says.html
The Spanish government doesn’t plan
to increase power prices for consumers for now,  ABC  reported,
citing an interview with Minister for Energy, Industry and
Tourism Jose Manuel Soria.  Soria said the government will try to make the cost of
electricity services “more reasonable,” according to the
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Angeline Benoit in Madrid  at 
 abenoit4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
